      "span_text": "Each culture was concentrated by centrifugation, mixed with sterile, prereduced PBS and glycerol to a final concentration of 20% glycerol, and frozen at −80°C in single-use aliquots. Gavage Rag1 −/− mice were placed on antibiotics at 3 to 4 weeks of age for 3 to 4 weeks. Antibiotic treatment consisted of ciprofloxacin (0.66 mg/ml), metronidazole (2.5 mg/ml; Sigma), and sugar-sweetened grape KoolAid Mix (20 mg/ml; Kraft Foods) in the drinking water [CITATION_2] ."
